1#pragma once
2#include <QJsonArray>
3#include <QJsonObject>
4#include <QJsonValue>
5#include <QList>
6#include <tuple>
7
8enum class QJsonIOPathType
9{
10 JSONIO_MODE_ARRAY,
11 JSONIO_MODE_OBJECT
12};
13
14typedef QPair<QString, QJsonIOPathType> QJsonIONodeType;
15
16struct QJsonIOPath : QList<QJsonIONodeType>
17{
18 template<typename type1, typename type2, typename... types>
19 QJsonIOPath(const type1 t1, const type2 t2, const types... ts)
20 {
21 AppendPath(t1);
22 AppendPath(t2);
23 (AppendPath(ts), ...);
24 }
25
26 void AppendPath(size_t index)
27 {
28 append({ QString::number(index), QJsonIOPathType::JSONIO_MODE_ARRAY });
29 }
30
31 void AppendPath(const QString &key)
32 {
33 append({ key, QJsonIOPathType::JSONIO_MODE_OBJECT });
34 }
35
36 template<typename t>
37 QJsonIOPath &operator<<(const t &str)
38 {
39 AppendPath(str);
40 return *this;
41 }
42
43 template<typename t>
44 QJsonIOPath &operator+=(const t &val)
45 {
46 AppendPath(val);
47 return *this;
48 }
49
50 QJsonIOPath &operator<<(const QJsonIOPath &other)
51 {
52 for (const auto &x : other)
53 this->append(x);
54 return *this;
55 }
56
57 template<typename t>
58 QJsonIOPath &operator<<(const t &val) const
59 {
60 auto _new = *this;
61 return _new << val;
62 }
63
64 template<typename t>
65 QJsonIOPath operator+(const t &val) const
66 {
67 auto _new = *this;
68 return _new << val;
69 }
70
71 QJsonIOPath operator+(const QJsonIOPath &other) const
72 {
73 auto _new = *this;
74 for (const auto &x : other)
75 _new.append(x);
76 return _new;
77 }
78};
79
80class QJsonIO
81{
82 public:
83 const static inline QJsonValue Null = QJsonValue::Null;
84 const static inline QJsonValue Undefined = QJsonValue::Undefined;
85
86 template<typename current_key_type, typename... t_other_types>
87 static QJsonValue GetValue(const QJsonValue &parent, const current_key_type &current, const t_other_types &...other)
88 {
89 if constexpr (sizeof...(t_other_types) == 0)
90 if constexpr (std::is_integral_v<current_key_type>)
91 return parent.toArray()[current];
92 else
93 return parent.toObject()[current];
94 else if constexpr (std::is_integral_v<current_key_type>)
95 return GetValue(parent.toArray()[current], other...);
96 else
97 return GetValue(parent.toObject()[current], other...);
98 }
99
100 template<typename... key_types_t>
101 static QJsonValue GetValue(QJsonValue value, const std::tuple<key_types_t...> &keys, const QJsonValue &defaultValue = Undefined)
102 {
103 std::apply([&](auto &&...args) { ((value = value[args]), ...); }, keys);
104 return value.isUndefined() ? defaultValue : value;
105 }
106
107 template<typename parent_type, typename t_value_type, typename current_key_type, typename... t_other_key_types>
108 static void SetValue(parent_type &parent, const t_value_type &val, const current_key_type &current, const t_other_key_types &...other)
109 {
110 // If current parent is an array, increase its size to fit the "key"
111 if constexpr (std::is_integral_v<current_key_type>)
112 for (auto i = parent.size(); i <= current; i++)
113 parent.insert(i, {});
114
115 // If the t_other_key_types has nothing....
116 // Means we have reached the end of recursion.
117 if constexpr (sizeof...(t_other_key_types) == 0)
118 parent[current] = val;
119 else if constexpr (std::is_integral_v<typename std::tuple_element_t<0, std::tuple<t_other_key_types...>>>)
120 {
121 // Means we still have many keys
122 // So this element is an array.
123 auto _array = parent[current].toArray();
124 SetValue(_array, val, other...);
125 parent[current] = _array;
126 }
127 else
128 {
129 auto _object = parent[current].toObject();
130 SetValue(_object, val, other...);
131 parent[current] = _object;
132 }
133 }
134
135 static QJsonValue GetValue(const QJsonValue &parent, const QJsonIOPath &path, const QJsonValue &defaultValue = QJsonIO::Undefined)
136 {
137 QJsonValue val = parent;
138 for (const auto &[k, t] : path)
139 {
140 if (t == QJsonIOPathType::JSONIO_MODE_ARRAY)
141 val = val.toArray()[k.toInt()];
142 else
143 val = val.toObject()[k];
144 }
145 return val.isUndefined() ? defaultValue : val;
146 }
147
148 template<typename parent_type, typename value_type>
149 static void SetValue(parent_type &parent, const value_type &t, const QJsonIOPath &path)
150 {
151 QList<std::tuple<QString, QJsonIOPathType, QJsonValue>> _stack;
152 QJsonValue lastNode = parent;
153 for (const auto &[key, type] : path)
154 {
155 _stack.prepend({ key, type, lastNode });
156 if (type == QJsonIOPathType::JSONIO_MODE_ARRAY)
157 lastNode = lastNode.toArray()[key.toInt()];
158 else
159 lastNode = lastNode.toObject()[key];
160 }
161
162 lastNode = t;
163
164 for (const auto &[key, type, node] : _stack)
165 {
166 if (type == QJsonIOPathType::JSONIO_MODE_ARRAY)
167 {
168 const auto index = key.toInt();
169 auto nodeArray = node.toArray();
170 for (auto i = nodeArray.size(); i <= index; i++)
171 nodeArray.insert(i, {});
172 nodeArray[index] = lastNode;
173 lastNode = nodeArray;
174 }
175 else
176 {
177 auto nodeObject = node.toObject();
178 nodeObject[key] = lastNode;
179 lastNode = nodeObject;
180 }
181 }
182
183 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<parent_type, QJsonObject>)
184 parent = lastNode.toObject();
185 else if constexpr (std::is_same_v<parent_type, QJsonArray>)
186 parent = lastNode.toArray();
187 else
188 Q_UNREACHABLE();
189 }
190};
